Biography

Career: Games played/started: 100/98...ranks eighth in putouts (500)...hit .289 with 105 hits, 54 runs, 21 doubles, eight home runs, 71 RBI, and three stolen bases...had a slugging percentage of .413 and an on-base percentage of .387...compiled a record of 2-2 in 12 appearances (seven starts) on the mound...had an ERA of 5.83 in 41.2 innings pitched...struck out 20 batters

Honors: 2012 All-SLC Second Team...2012 SLC All-Academic Second Team

2012: Games played/started: 55/55...All-SLC Second Team...SLC All-Academic Second Team... ranked second on team and tied for eighth in SLC with 40 RBI...hit .308 with a team leading 65 hits and 13 doubles...also collected 31 runs, four home runs, and three stolen bases...slugged .427 and had an on-base percentage of .392...went 2-for-3 with a double, two runs, and three RBI against SIE-Edwardsville on February 25th...went 2-for-3 with two steals, three runs, and an RBI agaisnt UTSA on April 28th...led team with 20 multi-hit games and had eight multi-RBI games

2011: Games played/started: 50/47...hit .263 with 23 runs, 40 hits, eight doubles, four home runs and 31 RBI...second on team with 29 walks and led the Bears with four sacrifice flies...went 2-2 with a 5.83 ERA in 12 appearances and seven starts on the mound...struck out 20 in 41.2 innings...drove in four with a double and a home run against Eastern Illinois on Feb. 20...also knocked in four with two hits, including a homer against Texas State on Apr. 10...struck out season-high seven and got the win in five inning start against Arkansas-Pine Bluff on Apr. 5...fanned six in six inning victory against Indiana State on Mar. 6

Previous College: Western States Conference Player of the Year in 2010 for Oxnard College in California...hit .331 with 40 runs, 45 hits, eight doubles, five home runs, 35 RBI and four stolen bases...had a .500 slugging percentage and .440 on-base percentage...also went 7-3 on the mound with a 2.57 ERA, 16 appearances, eight starts, four complete games and one shutout...struck out 46 and walked 16 in 73.2 innings...helped OC to a conference title with a 26-10 record

High School: played at Camarillo High School in California

Personal: son of Brad and Cathy Willson...major: Health Education
